TinyEMU: accept fence.tso (fm=1000) in the FENCE decoder.

The 2019 core's FENCE decode rejected any non-zero fm field
(mask 0xf00fff80), so fence.tso (fm=1000, base-ISA memory-ordering
fence) trapped as an illegal instruction. LLVM emits fence.tso for
C++ atomics, so e.g. clang SIGILL'd on startup while the GCC-built
base userland (which uses 'fence rw,rw', fm=0) ran fine. Drop bit 31
from the reject mask so fm=1000 is allowed; ordering is a nop in this
sequential interpreter. rs1/funct3/rd are still validated as zero.

--- a/riscv_cpu_template.h
+++ b/riscv_cpu_template.h
@@ -1351,8 +1351,13 @@
         case 0x0f: /* misc-mem */
             funct3 = (insn >> 12) & 7;
             switch(funct3) {
-            case 0: /* fence */
-                if (insn & 0xf00fff80)
+            case 0: /* fence / fence.tso */
+                /* fence.tso (fm=1000, bit 31) is base-ISA but post-dates this
+                 * 2019 core; the old mask 0xf00fff80 rejected any fm bits and
+                 * SIGILL'd it (LLVM emits fence.tso for C++ atomics, e.g. clang).
+                 * Allow fm=1000 too; ordering is a nop in this sequential
+                 * interpreter. Still validate rs1/funct3/rd are zero. */
+                if (insn & 0x700fff80)
                     goto illegal_insn;
                 break;
             case 1: /* fence.i */
